no-console.description:
Description

This rule disallows calls or assignments to methods of theconsoleobject.

Examples ofincorrectcode for this rule:

/* eslint no-console: "error" */

console.log("Log a debug level message.");
console.warn("Log a warn level message.");
console.error("Log an error level message.");
console.log = foo();

Examples ofcorrectcode for this rule:

/* eslint no-console: "error" */

// custom console
Console.log("Hello world!");

no-console.option:
This rule has an object option for exceptions:

- "allow"has an array of strings which are allowed methods of theconsoleobject

Examples of additionalcorrectcode for this rule with a sample{ "allow": ["warn", "error"] }option:

/* eslint no-console: ["error", { allow: ["warn", "error"] }] */

console.warn("Log a warn level message.");
console.error("Log an error level message.");
